        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"> This is a exact copy of a message I posted to VI.</P><P>There is currently only one major complaint that I have with EQ in all the classes that I play.</P><P>The horrible and totally unnecessary waste of time involved in travelling to and from Luclin.</P><P>I have long since given up on asking for Portals as porter classes are never available when you need them. I rely instead on the Luclin portal system.</P><P>However the time I am forced to waste waiting on the portals to activate is UNPLEASENT at best and downright INFURIATING at worst. Everyone I know feels the same way about this issue.</P><P>A long time ago I posted an idea to improve this experience however it was immediately censored off the boards.</P><P>Here it is again. Please consider it carefully as it would dramatically improve the game with no downside and no new spells or abilities or modifications that are not already in the game.</P><P>The portal idea.<BR>----------------</P><P>Have each Scoin respond to all direct hail's to them by immediatly giving a no rent "shard" to the player. Much the way the Norrath Scoins currently give a shard when told "Journey to Luclin".</P><P>This shard is then used as a key to only the spire at which it is issued. In order to activate the key the player clicks it on the spire. Or alternatively hands it back in as a trade to the Scoin.</P><P>The result of this click/trade is the consumption of the shard and the immediate portal of the player to the destination of the shard. The shard can only be clicked / handed in at the portal where it was issued.</P><P>This mechanism is already in place at places such as Skyshrine / Sebilis / Sleepers tomb / Charissis etc so no new mechanism are needed to implement it.</P><P>The effect of this would be that the current frustrating time waiting for the spires to activate would be eliminated. Reducing player frustration must be of paramount importance.</P><P>A future enhancement to this system would entail the introduction of additional "Scoins" in the Nexus. For example There is currently only one "Scoin" at the Nexus Antonica portal. This teleports you to NK. In order to provide a portal to WC all that would be needed would be a new "Scoin" standing at the Nexus Antonica Spire named "East Antonica Scoin".</P><P> </font></td>

