         To all of you posting fantasy reasons for the spires operating when they do. Thanks. My imagination is so limited I could never have thought of these amazing concepts myself. OMG Luclin is a moon and the spires can only port to it once every orbit - who whould have thought of such an amazing concept..... /sarcasm off</P><P>My point relates to enjoyment and entertainment. This is a game. It is supposed to be entertaining. Sitting on your hands for 15 minutes at a time is not entertaining, at least not to me. It is certainly not enjoyable.</P><P>Hunting an epic mob is a totally different thing. The satisfaction you get when your paitience is finally rewarded is, well reward in itself.</P><P>Personally I just don't get the same feeling of satisfaction when the Boat finally arrives or the portal finally activates.</P><P>Running from zone to zone is also totally different. I do it all the time with no feeling of frustration at all. There are always things happening during these runs. Nothing is happening while sitting on your hands waiting for a boat or a portal except frustration.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
