        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Traveling (boats) can be a pain.  I don't really mind running to a zone but waiting around doing nothing is a drag. What is really bad is sitting there, getting bored, reading a book and then looking up to see the boat leaving!!  Grrrr!  Of course, the same thing can be said about medding to a certain extent.  I tried Dark Age and the one thing I really liked about it was the reduced down time.</P><P>If I had my choice of reduced travel time or reduced med time, I would take the reduced med time hands down.  I think a 20% increase in the base mana recovery rate would not create any balance problems in the game and make the game more enjoyable.  Just my view though.  *shrug*</P><P>Vinsome Darkwalker<BR>Lady of Death, 28th Power<BR>Tholuxe Paxius</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
